BORDEAUX

Bordeaux is undoubtedly the most important wine-growing district in the world. At its best, it is a great wine of balance, richness and subtlety. Even when it is modest, provided it is authentic, it is at least a sound pleasing table wine.

Since “Bordeaux” is a geographical term one can approach it best through a map.

Study the map for several minutes and you will learn more than by reading pages of boresome description. Such phrases as ‘““Medoc,” “Sauternes,” “Margaux,” “Chateau Margaux” will assume a more logical, precise meaning.
